\begin_layout Standard
The traditional objective of the experimenter is to maximise the expected cumulative reward over a horizon of pulls, or equivalently, to minimise the 
\shape italic
regret
\shape default
 with respect to always pulling an optimal arm. Achieving this objective requires a careful balance between 
\shape italic
exploring
\shape default
 (to reduce uncertainty about the arms' expected rewards) and 
\shape italic
exploiting
\shape default
 (accruing high rewards). Regret-minimisation algorithms have been used in a variety of applications, including clinical trials
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{Robbins:1952}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, adaptive routing
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{Awerbuch+K:2008}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, and recommender systems
