\begin_layout Standard
Of separate interest is the problem of 
\shape italic
identifying
\shape default
 an arm with the highest mean reward
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{Bechhofer:1958,Paulson:1964,bib:evendar1}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, under what is called the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

pure exploration
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 regime. For applications such as product testing
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{Audibert+BM:2010}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and strategy selection
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{bib:sergiu}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, there is a dedicated phase in the experiment in which the rewards obtained are inconsequential. Rather, the objective is to identify the best arm either (1) in the minimum number of trials, for a given confidence threshold
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{bib:evendar1,bib:explorem}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, or alternatively, (2) with minimum error, after a given number of trials
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{Audibert+BM:2010,Carpentier+V:2015}
\end_layout

\end_inset

. Our investigation falls into the first category, which is termed the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fixed confidence
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 setting. Conceived by Bechhofer (
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citeyear{Bechhofer:1958}
\end_layout

\end_inset

), best-arm-identification in the fixed confidence setting has received a significant amount of attention over the years
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{bib:evendar1,Gabillon+GLB:2011,Karnin+KS:2013,Jamieson+MNB:2014}
\end_layout

\end_inset

. The problem has also been generalised to identify the best subset of arms
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
citep{bib:explorem,bib:lucb}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
